claim.claim-text:
1. A method of obtaining a plant with a doubled chromosome number comprising: 
a) obtaining a starting plant; 
b) treating said plant with a selected pressure of nitrous oxide gas during the stage of development of said plant during which formation of the floral primordium takes place; 
c) self pollinating the plant; and 
d) selecting a progeny plant with doubled chromosome number derived from the self pollinating.

46. A method of plant breeding comprising the steps of 
a) crossing at least a first and a second parent plant to produce a heterozygous plant comprising a selected genetic background; 
b) producing a haploid progeny plant derived from said hybrid plant; 
c) treating the haploid progeny plant with a selected pressure of nitrous oxide gas during the stage of development of said progeny plant during which formation of the floral primordium takes place; 
d) self pollinating the progeny plant; and 
e) selecting a doubled haploid progeny plant derived from the self pollinating, wherein the progeny plant has a desired genetic background.
